                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, June 26: The countrys forex reserves rose $3 billion for the week ended June 18 amid a sharp rise in foreign currency assets, the Reserve Bank said today. The reserves increased to $275.96 billion compared with $272.78 in the previous week, the RBI said in its weekly report.                             
	 Bangalore, June 26: Mahindra and Mahindra (M amp;M) plans to pump Rs 250 crore into the aerospace business. We are investing Rs 150 crore in the component business and Rs 100 crore in aircraft manufacturing, Anand Mahindra, vice-chairman and managing director of the group, said.                             
	 Washington, June 26: Reliance Powers request for $650 million in financing to build a coal-fired power plant in India has been rejected by the US Export-Import Banks board, spokesperson Stephanie OKeefe said.                                                                                                                          
